<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Johan Zietsman — Senior Software Engineer on the Sunshine Coast, Australia"
	pubDate={new Date()}
	hideMetadata={true}
>
	<p>
		Hey, I'm Johan — a Senior Software Engineer based on the Sunshine Coast, Queensland, Australia.
		I'm a polyglot developer who enjoys working across the stack, though my heart is in backend and
		distributed systems.
	</p>

	<p>
		My day-to-day involves building reliable, scalable software. I'm always exploring new languages,
		frameworks, and paradigms — lately I've been diving deeper into AI and how it's reshaping the way
		we build and ship software.
	</p>

	<p>
		This blog exists mostly as a personal reference — a place to document things I've learned so I
		can find them again later. If other developers find it useful along the way, even better.
	</p>

	<p>
		Outside of work, you'll find me enjoying the Sunshine Coast lifestyle — getting outdoors, pursuing
		creative hobbies, and hanging out with my two French Bulldogs.
	</p>
</Layout>
